message: Hey, don't beat yourself up so much. I know it feels like everything's awful right now, but it won't always be this way. Sometimes bad stuff happens because of one specific thing, not because you're a bad person. Maybe if you try to look at what *really* caused it, you'll see it's not something permanent about you.
reflection: Okay, so last year I totally bombed tryouts for the soccer team. I was convinced it was because I just wasn't good enough, like I'm just not athletic. But maybe it was because I was super stressed about exams that week and didn't practice as much as I should have. Also, I was dealing with that fight with my mom, so my head wasn't in the game. Focusing on those things makes it feel less like a permanent thing and more like a fixable problem, maybe if I try again this year and practice more I'll get in.
takeaway: I guess I need to stop being so hard on myself and remember that bad stuff happens, but it doesn't mean I'm a failure or something. I just need to look at the real reasons why things went wrong and try to fix them next time.

message: Hey, don't beat yourself up so much. I get that you're feeling bad right now, but one thing doesn't define you. Most of the time, stuff happens because of one thing at one time, not because you're just, like, a bad person or something. It's probably just a temporary thing, and you can totally deal with it and move on. Just try to figure out what really happened and don't think it's about who you are forever.
reflection: Okay, so last year I didn't make the varsity soccer team, and I was super bummed. I just thought it meant I was a terrible player and would never be good enough. But maybe if I thought about it differently, I could see that I just didn't train as hard as I should have that summer, or maybe the coach just had a different idea of what he wanted. If I focused on what I could change, like my training schedule, instead of just saying I'm bad, I could try again this year.
takeaway: I guess I need to remember that just because something bad happens doesn't mean I'm a bad person or that things will always be bad. There's usually a reason why things happen, and sometimes I can actually change it.

message: Hey, don't beat yourself up so much. It's easy to think one bad thing means you're just a failure or whatever, but that's probably not true. Most of the time, things happen because of one specific thing, like a bad test or a fight with someone. It doesn't mean you're a bad person or that things will always be awful. Things change, and you can make them better if you just focus on what actually went wrong this time.
reflection: Okay, so there was this time I didn't make the basketball team, and I was like, 'I'm just not good enough. I'm never gonna be good at anything.' But maybe it wasn't that I'm just a terrible player. Maybe I just didn't practice enough before tryouts, or maybe I was too nervous that day and choked. If I focus on those things, I could actually do something about it instead of just feeling bad about myself.

message: Hey, don't beat yourself up so much. It's easy to think that when something bad happens, it's like, a part of you or something. But most of the time it's just a specific thing that happened at a specific time. It doesn't mean you're a bad person or that it's always gonna be like this. Just try to figure out what exactly went wrong and you can totally fix it next time.
reflection: I remember when I didn't make the volleyball team. I thought it was because I just wasn't good enough, like I'm just not athletic or something. But maybe it was because I didn't practice as much that summer, or maybe I was just having an off day during tryouts. If I focus on those things, I could actually work on them and try out again next year instead of just giving up.

message: Hey, don't beat yourself up so much! Seriously, one bad thing doesn't mean you're a bad person or that you're gonna fail forever. Maybe this thing just happened because of, like, a specific reason or something that won't even matter next week. It's not you, it's probably just the situation. You're still awesome!
reflection: I failed my history test and I thought it was because I'm just dumb and can't learn that stuff. But maybe it's because I didn't study right or I was too tired that day to really focus. If I tried different ways to study, or just got more sleep, maybe I could actually do better next time. It doesn't have to mean I'm just bad at history forever.
takeaway: I need to remember that just because something bad happens, it doesn't mean I'm a failure. There's probably a reason why it happened, and I can try to fix it instead of just blaming myself.

message: Hey, don't beat yourself up about it. Seriously, stuff happens, right? It doesn't mean you're, like, a failure or anything. Maybe this one thing didn't work out, but that doesn't define you. It could just be bad timing or something specific happened that you can even fix next time.

If I focus on those things instead of just thinking I'm stupid, I could actually do better next time.

message: Hey, don't beat yourself up so much. Just because something bad happened doesn't mean it's, like, a permanent thing about you. Maybe it was just a one-time thing, or a misunderstanding, or you were just having an off day. Everyone messes up sometimes, but it doesn't mean you're a bad person or that things will always be this way. Try to think about what really caused it, and maybe you can fix it next time.
reflection: Okay, so last semester I got a really bad grade on my English paper and I was totally bummed. I started thinking I was just bad at writing and that I'd never be good at English. But, thinking about it now, maybe it wasn't just me being a bad writer. Maybe it was because I was super stressed out that week because of exams in other classes, and I didn't really focus on it or ask for help. So maybe next time I can plan better and actually ask for help from the teacher.
takeaway: I guess I should remember that just because I mess up sometimes, it doesn't mean I'm a failure or that things will always be bad. There's always a reason why things happen, and I can try to learn from it instead of just blaming myself.

message_to_friend: Hey, don't beat yourself up so much! I know things feel awful right now, but that doesn't mean it's gonna be like this forever. Sometimes bad stuff happens because of, like, one specific thing or a bad situation, not because you're a terrible person or anything. Think about what really caused it, maybe it was just a bad day or a misunderstanding. It doesn't define you, and things can totally get better.
personal_reflection: Okay, so there was this time I didn't make the soccer team, and I was convinced I was just a terrible player and would never be good at anything. But now that I think about it, maybe it was because I was super stressed about school at the time and wasn't practicing as much. Also, I had a cold right before tryouts, so I probably wasn't at my best. Focusing on those things, instead of just thinking I suck, makes me realize I could actually try again next year if I focus on practicing and not being sick, lol.
key_takeaway: I guess I need to remember that just because something bad happens, it doesn't mean I'm doomed forever. It's probably just a temporary thing, and I can work to change it instead of just giving up.

message: Hey, don't beat yourself up so much. One bad thing doesn't mean you're a bad person or that things will always be this way. Sometimes stuff just happens because of the situation, or maybe you were just having an off day. It's probably not some big flaw with you, just a temporary thing that you can learn from and move on from. Seriously.

But maybe it was just that I didn't prepare enough and was super nervous that day. If I practiced more and tried some relaxation techniques, maybe I could do better next time. It doesn't mean I'm doomed to be a bad speaker forever.
